[log] bash[68] stdout ### Node 5: Paper Download Lifecycle
[log] bash[68] stdout **Function Description**: Implement the complete paper download and conversion process, including status tracking and error handling.
[log] bash[68] stdout **Lifecycle Stages**:
[log] bash[68] stdout - Download the PDF file
[log] bash[68] stdout - Convert it to Markdown format
[log] bash[68] stdout - Track and update the status
[log] bash[68] stdout - Clean up temporary files
[log] bash[68] stdout **Input - Output Example**:
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout from arxiv_mcp_server.tools.download import handle_download, conversion_statuses
[log] bash[68] stdout # Complete download lifecycle test
[log] bash[68] stdout async def test_download_paper_lifecycle():
[log] bash[68] stdout     paper_id = "2103.12345"
[log] bash[68] stdout     
[log] bash[68] stdout     # Initial download request
[log] bash[68] stdout     response = await handle_download({"paper_id": paper_id})
[log] bash[68] stdout     status = json.loads(response[0].text)
[log] bash[68] stdout     assert status["status"] in ["converting", "success"]
[log] bash[68] stdout     
[log] bash[68] stdout     # Check the final status
[log] bash[68] stdout     response = await handle_download({
[log] bash[68] stdout         "paper_id": paper_id, 
[log] bash[68] stdout         "check_status": True
[log] bash[68] stdout     })
[log] bash[68] stdout     final_status = json.loads(response[0].text)
[log] bash[68] stdout     assert final_status["status"] in ["success", "converting"]
[log] bash[68] stdout # Download status response format
