[log] bash[68] stdout     error: Optional[str] = None
[log] bash[68] stdout ```
[log] bash[68] stdout ### Node 6: Existing Paper Handling
[log] bash[68] stdout **Function Description**: Handle repeated download requests for already downloaded papers to avoid redundant work.
[log] bash[68] stdout **Handling Strategy**:
[log] bash[68] stdout - Check local storage
[log] bash[68] stdout - Return the status of existing files
[log] bash[68] stdout - Provide the resource URI
[log] bash[68] stdout **Input - Output Example**:
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout # Existing paper test
[log] bash[68] stdout async def test_download_existing_paper():
[log] bash[68] stdout     paper_id = "2103.12345"
[log] bash[68] stdout     md_path = get_paper_path(paper_id, ".md")
[log] bash[68] stdout     
[log] bash[68] stdout     # Create a test markdown file
[log] bash[68] stdout     md_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
[log] bash[68] stdout     with open(md_path, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
[log] bash[68] stdout         f.write("# Existing Paper\nTest content")
[log] bash[68] stdout     
[log] bash[68] stdout     response = await handle_download({"paper_id": paper_id})
[log] bash[68] stdout     status = json.loads(response[0].text)
[log] bash[68] stdout     assert status["status"] == "success"
[log] bash[68] stdout # Existing paper response
